had my wisdom teeth cut out this morning and one of my stitches came lose should i be worried i got my wisdom teeth out this morning my appt was set for around by i was at home i'm guessing it was something around pm that my mom brought me in my pills and a glass of water well when i went to put the pill in my mouth i guess i opened my mouth alittle too far i hear a weird noise and wasn't positive what it was well it ended up being my stick partially coming out i can feel part of it hanging down and it's kind of annoying rubbing against my cheek is this something i should be worried about being so soon after surgery or should it heal up fine anyways hi i've been in dentistry for over years the best thing to do is bite on the gauze until you have zero bleeding once that happens the suture is of no concern but to stop dry socket do not suck or rinse for hours once that goes by start with warm salty water rinses times a day the last at night before bed gently this removes dried blood bacteria and any food stuck to the extraction area do this for week sleep with an extra pillow and towel if you are still bleeding do not eat any food eat ice cream and cold cool things no straws after days gently eat soft foods that do not stick ice pack with cloth cover on every hour for minutes the first hours then times a day after do not smoke don't spit it will heal fine now after days start massaging the jaw and open your mouth like to yawn don't go tooooooo far this will begin to lossen up the jaw muscles and stop the swelling and pain keep this up after days you can eat a bit more but be careful keep up the salt water rinses brush and floss if you follow these directions you should be in pretty good shape after days if you have any other questions please ask marie Wisdom teeth Tooth First aid Breastfeeding Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Wound Textile manufacturing Halitosis Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Shark Mouth ulcer Cheese Shaggy dog story Stomach cancer Vampire 